text:
green is my favourite colour i must say. i walked into this market shop and decided to indulge into a bit of shopping in a foreign land. turkey, in belek to be precise. a town with less women on the streets leaving boisterous men selling different types of merchandise. even the ladies up and about are mostly tourists just like me. so inside the shop i spotted a jungle green dress and i got smitten. i picked it, tried it and it was perfect. but the dress has it's own story. a tale that happens everyday everywhere in the world. a sad narrative. one so sad that i threw away the dress to avoid memories but at the same time posted it publicly to raise awareness. 
to be continued..

text:
tarana burke is a civil rights activist who was the original founder of the "me too" movement, which she started in 2006. it later became a global phenomenon that raised awareness about sexual harassment, abuse, and assault in society in 2017.

tarana burke was born september 12, 1973 in the bronx, ny. she is an african-american civil rights activist. she's most well-known as the founder of the "me too" movement in 2006 which has blossomed into a worldwide campaign to raise awareness about sexual harassment, abuse, and assault in society. in 2017 burke and other influential female activists were named "the silence breakers" by time magazine. she currently serves at the girls for gender equity in brooklyn as its senior director. #metoomovement #metoo #civilrightsmovement #blackhistory365

text:
nu är det dags för omgång två! 
dessa boxar är alla hjärtans dag-inspirerade.
idag 14/2 och imorgon 15/2 är boxen 10kr billigare, alltså kostar boxen då 139kr/st.
sista dag att beställa är 28/2-19!

alla hjärtans dag box 1
en bok med en viktig handling som snuddar ämnet #metoo och är en riktigt bra bok, enligt mig. det är en ungdomsbok, men passar egentligen de flesta pga. ämnet den berör.
boken är dessutom signerad!!
boken är i flexband

alla hjärtans dag box 2
en bok om ett hemskt felsteg/skada som skakat hela författarens familj. det är en biografi som är allvarsam och gripande. ena stunden gråter man, nästa kokar man av ilska. det är en bok som berör sjukvårdens fel och brister men även hur man kan se ljuspunkter i vardagen efter en hemsk olycka.
boken passar de flesta, men kanske inte personer yngre än 15 år. 
boken är inbunden

text:
a kind of love story. of self love and preservation. and if we're here for love then we gotta look at all the ways it is expressed. it's been 25 years since 24 year old ecuadorian immigrant lorena bobbit chopped her rapist husband's dick right off.

i was 13, i remember the jokes and i'm sure i laughed. a dismembered dick? gross! weird! but i'd also already had so many strangers flash their shriveled and weird shaped parts at me, grab at me, that i felt some quiet satisfaction in knowing she'd done something about it.

there's a great story about her in @nymag with 4 brilliant writers penning their own sort of love letters to her. letters of understanding and empathy and solidarity. because her struggle is ours too. oh, and a documentary is coming out on friday.

happy galentine's day, y'all. take no shit. stand with your sisters. there is no justice without love. 🗡🗡🗡🗡❤❤❤❤👭🏻👭🏽👭🏼👭🏾👭👭🏿

text:
day 14 of sexual abuse in the black community:

tyler perry "in addition to the brutal physical abuse, tyler says he also suffered severe sexual abuse at the hands of four different adults.

tyler says he was 5 or 6 years old the first time he was molested. while building a birdhouse with an adult male neighbor, the man put his hands in tyler's pants, he says. "i'm thinking, 'what is this?'" tyler says. "and i felt my body betraying me, because i felt an erection at that age." tyler says he later endured sexual molestation at the hands of a male nurse and a man he knew from church. "[the man from church] used god and the bible against me to justify a lot of the things that were going on. it was so horrible," tyler says. "and that was my first sexual experience, with this man performing oral sex on me as a boy." read more here: https://www.oprah.com/oprahshow/tyler-perry-speaks-out-about-being-molested-and-the-aftermath

#onetouchtransformation #blackhistorymonth #blackcommunity #sexualabuseawareness #rape #molestation #csa #survivor #metoo #tylerperry #awareness #prevention #abuse #mentoo #menhurttoo #malesurvivors

text:
during the 36-year-long guatemalan civil war, #indigenous women were systematically raped and enslaved by the military in a small outpost near the #sepurzarco community. what happened to them then was not unique, but what followed, changed history. from 2011, fifteen women survivors fought for justice at the highest court of guatemala. finally, in 2016, two former military officers were convicted of sexual violence, and sexual and domestic slavery. they were sentenced to 120 and 240 years of imprisonment, which included an additional thirty years in prison for both defendants for crimes against humanity, in recognition of the importance of punishing gender-based violence. this was the first time that wartime sexual violence was tried in the country, as well as the first time a national court ruled in a domestic and sexual slavery case.
now this process is under threat as the guatemalan congress is planning to grant blanket #amnesty to all wartime crimes against humanity. as a response, thirty-six maya-achí women survivors are challenging the proposed law in the constitutional court of guatemala. they ask the court to stop the bill because “it represents an attempt to manipulate the law to evade justice and to achieve impunity”. pictured: one reparation measure for the sepur zarco community that has had some traction is the free mobile health clinic, which serves 70 – 80 people every day. “we had to walk long to get to a clinic, but now it’s closer. each community takes turn to take care of the clinic. many women from my community have received medicines, but there are sicknesses that cannot be treated here…we dream of a hospital that can treat all our illnesses,” explained rosario xo, one of the survivors.

go to our story to read more about sepur zarco women!

photo: un women/ryan brown

preliminary reports suggested that the blast occurred at 3 p.m. when the crpf convoy, carrying dozens of jawans, was moving on the highway. crpf inspector general said a vehicle laden with explosives hit the convoy.

terror outfit jaish-e-muhammad (jem) has claimed responsibility for the attack, saying it was a suicide blast. a jem spokesman said its cadre adil ahmad dar alias waqas carried out the bombing. it was not immediately clear if dar was in the vehicle when it exploded.

text_retweet:
this is powerful

#repost @flygurl96 (@get_repost)
・・・
today in black sistory we honor the silence 
we the silent screams of our foremothers
the screams swallowed 
while we were raped 
the screams tucked into the darkest places 
of our souls 
so as not to wake the children 
and see more horror in their eyes 
so as not to wake the men 
and see the pain of not being able to protect us 
the emasculation of being powerless 
when master rapes your wife 
we the sobs hushed 
we the refrains muffled 
we the words that didn’t part from our teeth 
because 
we did best to know our place 
we did best not to be uppity 
or think that we may deserve dignity 
we that learned a down cast eye 
kept us alive 
we the tears flowing like waterfalls 
perpetually inside 
while our sons swung 
high 
and died 
our feet bleed beneath our skin 
our backs shredded within 
our lips closed and tight 
our tongue tattooed with perpetual bite 
we learned to suffer in silence to save ourselves
to save our men and children 
we learned too well 
we the tired 
we the weary
we the screams
we the sirens
we are silent no more 
you will hear us 
our feet marching 
with the screams of our ancestors at our backs 
like wind in our sails 
vengeance that has laid waiting for too long 
we will open our mouths 
and you will never hear the same again 
our screams will echo in your souls forever 
our #metoo began before hollywood 
before trump grabbed pussies 
stand with your alabaster tears 
for as long as you can 
but move when you hear my army 
move when you hear my battle cry 
move when you feel the presence of my lineage 
silent no more --leslé honoré

text:
virginia lt. gov. fairfax’s accuser speaks on stanford #metoo panel
#
a college professor avoided talking directly about her accusation that virginia's lieutenant governor sexually assaulted her, but she talked in detail about her research and thoughts on the growing number of women reporting abuse."one thing that i notice with sexual violence is that there are many people who would like to glance away from this," vanessa tyson told a stanford university symposium. "it's one of the ugliest parts of humanity. trust me."tyson, appearing tuesday night as one of two panelists at the event called "betrayal and courage in the age of #metoo", was making her first public appearance since she accused virginia lt. gov. justin fairfax of assaulting her in 2004. tyson is a political science professor at southern california's scripps college who is spending a year at stanford as a research fellow.fairfax said he recalled the encounter, which he said was consensual, and denied assaulting or coercing tyson."perhaps we have to reshape how we understand consent and how we teach it to society as a whole," tyson said during her talk, which also included her experience with students who were sexually assaulted confiding in her, and the difficulty victims have when institutions don't appear to take their claims seriously."speaking…

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
begging  is the practice of imploring others to grant a favor, often a gift of money with little or no expectation of reciprocation. a person doing such is called a beggar, panhandler, or mendicant. street beggars may be found in public places such as transport routes, urban parks, and near busy markets. besides money, they may also ask for food, drink, cigarettes or other small items.
begging is illegal under the vagrancy act of 1824. however it does not carry a jail sentence and is not well enforced in many cities, although since the act applies in all public places it is enforced more frequently on public transport.
.
.
.

text: @mandymooremm i want you to know that you are so brave for speaking up about the abuse you went through. i hear you. i see you. and i stand with you. as someone who has gone through sexual harassment/assault, shaming and bullying (which i would call this verbal abuse). this breaks my heart. i am dedicated to making sure women do not have to through this alone. a forever goal of mine, is to help women who have gone through trauma. i want to reach out to women and help them as much as i possibly can. if i can do that——inspire women, and help make a difference through my writing or blog posts then that will make me so so happy! i hope that no woman has to go through this alone. especially the other handful of women (@_fake_nudes_ , @tropicalijaye, @littlestmonkey ) who have come forward to share their stories for the @nytimes. so, my wish is for all women of trauma to join me and come together, to support one another, and be there for each other. because, you are not alone. 💕🌈 also, if you have experienced any abuse, sexual assault, harassment, etc. please feel free to contact me at brittanyanndobbins@gmail.com, or dm me on insta. i will do my very best to help you through your trauma and give you some friendly advice! although i am not a therapist, i am here for you and i will listen to you. 💕 so pls chat with me! :) @nytimes #ryanadams #mandymoore #thisisus #sexualharassment #metoomovement #metoo #timesup #feminism #womensupportingwomen #femaleempowerment #musicindustry #beauty #activism #advocacy #writer #sisterhoodforever #inspire #motivation #womeninpower #advice #trauma #musicindustry

text:
@contemporaryathon photo challenge day three: favourite nonfiction contemporary 💛 every essay in this anthology is so important and timely.
.
.
.
"there's this impossible paradox when you are victimized by sexual assault. you want to - you have to - convince yourself that it wasn't that bad in order to have any hope of healing. if it really is as bad as you feel like it is, how will you ever get out from under it? how will you ever get better? on the other hand, you need to convince others it was bad enough to get the help and support you need to do that healing. to get out from under it. to get an appointment at the clinic. to get friends to come over with styrofoam food containers when you can't feed yourself. you tell yourself how bad it is and then you numb yourself to how bad it is. you repeat as needed for so many years. does saying no 16 times make me worthy of pity? does it make me worthy of help?" - excerpt from "to get out from under it" by stacey may fowles
.
.
.

text:
violence against women 
would you believe it if i told you that over 90% of women in sri lanka are subject to sexual harassment in public transport?
if i told you that over 60% of women in sri lanka are subject to domestic violence?
if i told you that over 40% of women in sri lanka are subject to some form of violence every single day?
✖️
sri lanka may be a champion when it comes to having elected the first female prime minister and being ranked better than our neighboring countries in the gender inequality index.
nevertheless, there are many underlying and prevailing issues pertaining to gender inequality in sri lanka.
✖️
while women are the majority population and in most sectors the backbone of the economy, we are continued to be dismissed for our opinions and rights to equality.
✖️
despite all the suppression and inequality, there are many incredible women out there breaking stereotypes and demanding their rights. ✖️
tag someone you know and let them know they are not in this fight alone 💪🏽✨
.
.
.
.
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
as my grandma connie used to say: "what's love got to do with it?" // don't spend any more time loving someone who doesn't deserve it--even if....
.
.
you aren't a bad person for walking away. you aren't responsible to heal their trauma, you weren't  put on the earth for them or to be this person's punching bag or to satisfy anyone's inner demons.
.
.
even if you love them, even if they're struggling with their behavior upon reflection, even if they're trying to stop hurting you, or can't help but hurt you because 'when he was a kid;' even if he upholds himself as "minnesota nice"
.
.
you're not abandoning a victim by identifying ways in which they've abused you -- and removing yourself. maybe they'll find a therapist to help them heal someday 👍 or maybe not. it's not your problem! but they've probably somehow made you feel as though it is.
.
.
it's never wrong to protect yourself. it's easy to be blindsighted by compassion, understanding for another person's plight. to feel, like i did, that being an advocate means accepting abusive people into your home and heart and bed. to feel, like i did, that rage and obsession and control and uncontrollable sexual urges are signs of unbridled love. to feel, like i did, that one act of forgiveness was a contract that i must always forgive him.
.
protect yourself from being sucked into someone elses cycle of abuse. protect yourself against cyclical behaviors that result from previous traumas. being abused doesn't inherently mean a person will inflict trauma upon another; it's a special kind of fucked up to pass along sexual abuse from their body to your body.
.
soooo, bottom line, if you think your partner's past is hurting you....then....leave (easier said than done tho right?). then find yourself a good therapist so you don't sabatoge ur future.
.
.
here's to emdr, which helped me untangle myself from a person i thought i left years ago, and here's to dr young for helping me reframe it all so i could heal; and here's to loving myself and accepting my story a little more every day.
.
here and 💯 not judging if anyone wants to talk about anything.
.
.
#survivornotvictim #emdr #cptsdrecovery #valentinesday2019 #metoo

text:
hark! over the horizon. a mighty fiend! it skulks over as it feels hiraeth for its long lost village. such ephemeral nonsense cannot escape me. this ruse has much to be worked upon. i grin with my slightly crooked teeth, and approach the beast. again, i see past its cromulent tears and slay it. as i look over yonder to the blazing sun, the temporarily defeated monstrosity takes a snapshot of my malicious countenance. it flees into the baobab tree, pleading for permanent solitude. and so, i move on.

a #metoo effect.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i don’t share this often, but my first binge that i can clearly remember happened in elementary school. i sat at the island at my dad’s new house and ate the cereal my mom never allowed at home: lucky charms.
.
the weekends i spent at my dad’s house were the loneliest moments of my life - i can’t even express the deep loneliness to you. it was so traumatic to me that i swear i had ptsd until recently, where i feel like i’ve finally dealt with 90% of it. .
but the junk food made me happy for a second. i swear this is how the eating disorder stuff all started. swinging from “healthy” foods loaded with diet terms at mom’s to fast food and super-processed junk food at my dad’s + trying to navigate the world of being a girl in a really effed up family situation. .
even just thinking about being that little girl again makes me want to cry as i write this. when i revisit that memory, i feel more alone than i ever have in my entire life. .
but things are a billion trillion times better now. that girl grew up and became someone i am proud to be ❤️
.
i want to share that with you because get it. 
i went through my parent’s terrible divorce. 
i was sexually abused by another child who was also being sexually abused. 
i had step sisters who had the opposite bodies as me and watched them get attention while i torturously compared myself to them every. single. day. 
i didn’t know how to make friends. 
i felt alone. 
i cried myself to sleep. 
i didn’t understand how to love myself. 
i never learned how to be bree.
.
i didn’t even mean for this to be so raw, i guess it’s been too long since the last time i spoke about it. .
if you’re reading this, i see you. and i don’t care where your pain is coming from. if you’ve been through worse or if you don’t even feel like you’ve been through anything, it doesn’t matter. if you’re struggling, you don’t have to justify your pain.
.
but you are stronger than the pain. sometimes you just need support so you can see that. reach out. reach out until you’re heard. it took my mom, my boyfriend, and sharing my story in this community for me to finally be able to move forward. it’s okay to need help. never be ashamed of needing help❤️

text:
✨soul up self love✨⁣
⁣
i applaud every single person who has ever found themselves in a dark place but rose above the pain and chose love instead. ⁣
⁣
it’s not easy choosing to do the hard work of loving yourself enough to dive deep into the black abyss of fear in order to conquer it one small thought and action at a time. ⁣
⁣
we live in a world that has become accustomed to just putting a band aid ⁣
over anything uncomfortable. fear, pain, disease and even love. ⁣
⁣
if needed, i challenge you to course correct starting now! ⁣
⁣
trauma creates change we don’t choose. ⁣
healing creates change we choose. ⁣
⁣
choose to heal. ⁣
choose to love. ⁣
choose to live. ⁣
⁣
choose to soul up! ✨💞🙌🏻⁣
⁣
tips to start your soul up journey⁣
⁣
1. have an open, beginners mindset. ⁣
2. meditate. creating stillness inside. ⁣
3. release suppressed emotions. ⁣
4. practice methodical, conscious breathing. ⁣
5. start to gain awareness of your thoughts, beliefs and judgments. ⁣
6. learn to trust your intuition. gut instinct is usually soul instinct. ⁣
7. do things you love everyday. ⁣
⁣
i will be launching a soul up self love digital course in march to dive deeper into all of this. 💗💗💗⁣
⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

‏اینجا ایرانه، جایی که به خاطر «عشق» باید پشت میله های زندان باشی، جایی که به خاطر «حق» خودت ممکنه اعدام بشی، جایی که همجنسگراها «آزادی» ندارن... اینجا ایرانه!

دگرباشان همچون همه انسان‌های دیگرند و با وجود حق انتخابی که دارند و باید داشته باشند، بر اساس گرایشات خود تصمیم می‌گیرند با هم جنس خود زندگی کنند یا دیگری! که متأسفانه در ایران این حق به شدت از آنها سلب شده! .
هر لحظه زیستن ما همجنسگرایان، مبارزه مداوم است. علیه تحجر، مردسالاری، جنسیت زدگی، نرم‌محوری، دگرجنسگرامحوری ما با بودنمان نفس کشیدنمان عشق ورزیدنمان و زیستن به عنوان بخشی از یک جامعه انسانی فریادی از تغییر و پیشروی هستیم.
تغییر به سمت برابری🌈 و آزادی...
.
طرح از رضا عقیلی 
#عشق_عشقه 
#lgbt #metoo #valentinesday2019

text:
“it’s been a very difficult thing being a lead singer of a rock band looking like me and it still is. i have to say it’s been a fight and it will always be a fight. that fight is interesting and that fight drives you and makes you want to work harder. i want to say to any new artists out there, man you’re in for a ride. it’s not going to be easy, it’s not supposed to be easy, it’s the friggin’ music business and you’re women, and some of you are black and some of you are gay like me. you’ve got to keep moving forward, keep striving for everything you want to be. keep being very, very individual and doing exactly what you want.” double-platinum selling frontwoman of skunk anansie -skin, receiving the inspirational artist award at the @musicweekinsta women in music awards, november 2018. .
.
.
.
.

text:
amar a dios sobre todas las cosas, amar a tu familia,amar a tus hijos, amar tu trabajo, amar a una pareja y a tu mascota ....son todos amores cuyo desenvolvimiento, crecimiento y satisfacción vienen dados por lo sólido, real , positivo y verdadero que sea tu amor propio, que si cojea de una pata, esa pequeña falla en el valor y amor que a ti te asignas se reflejará  en el área correspondiente .
por eso y sin necesidad de rayar en el egoísmo narcisista, invierte tiempo, acciones y dinero en conocerte,aceptarte y disfrutarte para que luego de haber cimentado con buenas bases  tu amor propio  tengas con qué practicar (y no solo predicar) los otros amores. sino te amas de la forma más perfecta, amarás mal al prójimo y a dios.
superarte es un súper arte !

text:
ritual abuse is a problem you don't see on the news very much 
going to read a few papers and see whether this is a topic covered in a credible database .. you don't get much research on this topic.

yet the problem is larger than people think because a bunch of children go missing every year. so where do you think they're all going? and why haven't these criminals been caught. 
maybe it's cos the whole ring circulates our government, judicial and regulatory bodies - i mean they've already found evidence of this in the past...look at britain.. so the issue is ongoing yet i don't see people concerned about it on the news. can't trust the powers that be and unfortunately they're the people who control what it is we all see on the news.. not everyone in government, judiciary and regulatory bodies are bad, but lots of them are psychopaths. you can argue that by doing five mins of research into psychopaths and then use your own logic to realise that these people are going to infiltrate positions of authority. and once they're in they get their cult friends in. pedogate is a mathematical probability, not a conspiracy.

text:
yesterday we talked about developing a safety plan that outlines the ground rules and behaviors you will adopt as the primary caregivers for your children in order to keep them safe from sexual abuse. today, the question is how do you communicate with your family and other individuals who have access to your children what your safety plan entails and your expectations of them with regard to how they interact with your children?
1) be intentional. make a point to have an open and honest conversation with your family members, close family friends, and others. let them know you are concerned about your children's safety and you need their help and cooperation by adhering to a few "ground rules" that are designed to help prevent your children from being sexually abused.
2) point out problematic behaviors that you have noticed in the past without being accusatory. you may say something like "we really love to see how much fun the kids have playing with the family during family gatherings, we just ask that everyone refrain from playing the tickle game with them".
3) be willing to speak up when family members and others violate your safety plan. crossing boundaries is a key component in how predators groom children and their families. nip problematic behaviors in the bud immediately so your children don't become accustomed to having people touch them in inappropriate ways or being subjected to sexually explicit materials or conversation.
4) be willing to withdraw access to your children from anyone who is unwilling to adhere to your safety plan or consistently violates it.
what other ways can you think of that you can communicate with your family, friends, teachers, coaches, church leaders, physicians etc about your safety plan? #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #superbowl

text:
never ever ever let anyone tell you you’re incomplete on your own. all those princess fairytales, the beliefs of older generations... they served their purpose, but it’s time to uplevel now.
.
i don’t usually acknowledge valentine’s day, but it’s all around us, emphasizing this same lesson, so i thought i’d share that this is something i’ve been working on in my personal life for awhile now.

text:
love? my world is full of it. love isn't always - and often isn’t, for me - connected to sex or romance at all. eros, philia, agape... love surrounds us in all shapes and forms. i couldn’t be be more grateful for the love i've found in the deep, compassion-filled friendships i've encountered over the past years. i made a terrifying leap in 2017 to live more vulnerably, authentically, out in the open, not knowing who would love me through it. coming out about my history as a trauma survivor was one of the scariest things i've ever done, but it freed me to openly walk this journey i'm on of learning to reclaim my body, my sense of touch and intimacy. and that side of love may take time, trust, and patience for me. but when i made that leap towards truth, i landed in the arms of a community that taught me the beauty of love without expectation or judgement. to be seen and honored for who you really are, and to be blessed with the opportunity to offer that same gift to others - that, to me, is the most beautiful love of all. happy agape day, today, tomorrow, and every other day. i love you all. 💕

and now for a john o'donohue quote:
"anam cara means soul friend. the anam cara was a person to whom you could reveal the hidden intimacies of your life. this friendship was an act of recognition and belonging. when you had an anam cara, your friendship cut across all convention and category. you were joined in an ancient and eternal way with the friend of your soul. in this love, you are understood without mask or pretension. the superficial and functional lies and half-truths of social acquaintance fall away, you can be as you really are. love allows understanding to dawn, and understanding is precious. where you are understood, you are at home. understanding nourishes belonging. when you really feel understood, you feel free to release yourself into the trust and shelter of the other person's soul." #love #friendship #agape #agapelove #survivor #metoo #healingjourney #demisexualpride #demiromanticpride #demisexual #demiromantic  #valentines

text:
all i do is live and breathe art so why not dedicate a series of interviews featuring other creatives. there is really no reason not to! so today i am launching artists i admire! 🌟
with these interviews i want to bring us together, building larger and stronger creative communities. i want us all to gain by getting to know more artists, learn about who they are, why they practice, and what they may recommend for others as they manage their own career as an artist. 🌟
my first interview in this series is with bunny portia, a painter that explores self-portraiture and concepts of youth and beauty in her art. around her 60th birthday, she started making a series called momento mori. so many of us within the twin cities art community got hooked on what she was making. we haven’t stopped wanting to see more from her! so, please enjoy getting to know bunny portia!
🌟
the link is located on my profile page! 
follow bunny portia: @bunnyportia

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: in today’s society it’s safer to be kissed by a dog than a man. in sweden, the most gender equal country in the world, a woman is accused of drug abuse. the drug was found in her blood when she was in the hospital after being raped by a swedish police officer and they did a rape kit on her. she was drugged. the police officer is well connected in the city of västerås in sweden where this is going on right now, he has connections high up in the justice departement and is from a family of police men, her accusation on him for rape was disused even though she managed to call 911 during the rape, even though the police came and found them during the action of rape. the justice system is wrong so is the respect of woman in today’s society. come on sisters, let’s start standing up for eachother. passivity obviously does not take us anywhere. it’s 2019 after #metoo and this is still going on. we need to change this by not accepting abusive behavior in anyway. #timesup #sistersquad #sisterforsister #förjenny #myvalentine #standingupforeachother #enoughisenough #feminismisnecessary

text:
this post is in response to a black female perspective.
➖
everything should be put in context. the accounts listed are facts. however, the conclusion on page 6 alludes to: extrapolation of the behavior of famous stars onto the general population is a recommendation.
➖
to imagine the average black man had behavior similar to those men mentioned in her story is not only opinion, it's a baseless opinion. whether it's yesteryear or today, black folk have a horrible tendency to live vicariously through celebrities being unable to approximate not only the financial wealth of their celebrity idol, but also the social status necessary to be immune to criticism and public scorn.
➖
at the time of the accounts listed, black families were still practicing mostly conservative christian social values. and at that time, those stars produced what was accused as secular "devil's" music. so it's unlikely, and even highly improbable the average black woman was being used as a "stepping stone" by the average black man.
➖
anyway, it's good to have the truth out in the open so we can process the corresponding emotion and sociopolitical implications.
➖
because the truth of the matter leads black folk to conclude: any struggle to assimilate into white society will be accompanied with deviant behavior because white society (mostly white capital) will pressure black men and women until deviant behavior is identified, and then white capital will reward those deviants with fame and fortune. which will allow the deviant behavior to continue with impunity; that is, until a #metoo strategy can be worked out in favor of white supremacy.
➖
so i believe the best recommendation after viewing these accounts, is to imagine what was the average black family life like. what was the average black family struggling with. (rather than to suppose that the average black female was being oppressed by the average black man.)
➖
a socio-political-economic revolution of the black collective consciousness is what is necessary here. we must evolve beyond so called american moral ideals. this is part of us developing our own culture and social justice. #blacknationalism #blackempowerment

text:
a break from my usual posts but i love this so i had to share!
➖
i am a champion for justice, but my reason for loving this today boils down to two words! marianne williamson. she is the spiritual teacher & activist behind the famous ‘our deepest fear is not that we are inadequate’ quote. (google it!).
➖
well known in the spiritual/human potential circles, i am excited that she is in the race because of who she is likely to influence. people like my friend liza!*
➖
marianne is the only person who could actually nudge liza out of her current ‘rainbows and unicorns only’ existence and get her to vote. 🙈liza insists on living this way because she does not want to attract bad energy. to ensure this, she doesn’t watch tv or read news & doesn’t give a rat’s bottom about politics.🤨 she does not vote! to me this equals giving up her civic right to be a part of policies that will affect the future of her children in exchange for a ‘right-now-zen like’ existence.
➖
but why do i care? well, one, she is my friend. two, she is as sharp as a tack. previously a top notch lawyer about to make partner in a new york city firm, she quit her role when she realized she was pregnant with her first child, lucy. after child birth, she decided that she did not want to get back to the cut throat law environment. now she is a reiki healer and lives a totally mellow life.
➖
you probably know someone who like liza, has made a complete 180 degree career & lifestyle turnaround (the robin sharma effect aka the monk who sold his ferrari). a top notch surgeon one day and a tantric coach the next!
➖
it is my hope that liza will now be influenced by ‘the marianne effect’. i yearn for her to ‘wake up’ and take charge of what’s happening around her. even if it looks grim in the beginning, i know she can best handle it by being a part of the solution.
➖
and in the end, whether mw wins or not, at least the final tally will hopefully be more representative of everyone’s votes (including liza’s) & transcending all gender, faith and racial composition.
➖
do you have a friend like liza? thoughts about the current possibilities in the political front?

p.s. to liza, i love you! 💕
(* not her real name).

text:
❤️?? idag är det en dag i kärlekens tecken, men inte för alla. har du någonsin tänkt på det? många kallar det de gör för sex. det är inte sex. det är sexuella övergrepp. jag har i över ett decennium jobbat i den ideella sektorn för brottsutsattas upprättelse. nu som målsägandebiträde och brottoffersamordnare. tidigare inom uppsala kvinnojour. jag har sett och hört sådant som jag önskar inte existerade i denna värld. det gör det. jag bär på hemligheter om andra som jag aldrig kan berätta för någon. jag lever bakom kulisserna, jag vet hur mörkret ser ut för de som utsätts. jag fortsätter att kämpa. jag ger inte upp. vad kan jag göra mera? du kanske kan svara på det? jag har och kommer alltid att jobba brottspreventivt. 
kom ihåg att alla former av tvång, direkt eller indirekt, som medför ofrivillig beröring är övergrepp. en minderårig kan aldrig samtycka till "sex". med det sagt vill jag ändå önska er som firar alla hjärtans dag med kärlek och respekt - grattis på alla hjärtans dag. till dig som vill prata med mig i egenskap av målsägandebiträde hör gärna av dig. jag företräder barn och vuxna.🌸

text:
💔💔if valentine’s is really hard for you💔💔this morning i am donating ✨distance reiki✨ to you. ✨✨just dm me or comment below✨✨ whether you’re struggling because of loss or loneliness, valentine’s can feel like salt in an open wound for a lot of people. 
no matter how smart, strong and successful you are, i’ve been there and i know much valentine’s can amplify feelings of heartbrokenness.💔 so i’m offering up some time today during which i will do collective distance reiki for everyone here who is struggling through valentine’s, and wants to receive some support in this way. 💔💔here’s how it’ll work:

1. if you would like to receive some free collective distance reiki today, dm me or comment below.

2. this morning i will do a distance session for everyone who has asked me. **i will structure it so that if you comment or message me after i’ve done the session, you will still receive distance reiki today. ‼️if you are in crisis, please seek immediate emergency assistance. if you’re in canada or the us, there are some crisis text numbers below. if you’re anywhere else, please call your local emergency number. ‼️the crisis text line organization provides 24/7, confidential text messaging for people in crisis. a crisis worker will text you back immediately and keep texting with you to help bring you from a hot moment to a calm place.

if you’re in canada: text 686868.

if you’re in the us: text home to 741741.

hold on, breathe deeply, and know that less heavy days can still be yours.

fyi, some additional info on my donation of reiki this week - if you’re not familiar, reiki is love, light and healed information. it goes where it is most needed. i am a reiki master (you can look me up on the cdn reiki assoc. website if you want more info about which style i practice). #valentinesblues #heartbroken #valentinessucks #metoo #trauma #survivor #freereiki #distancereiki #grief #grieving #loss #reiki #lightworker #loveandlight

både barn och vuxna behöver lära sig att varje människa har en ovillkorlig rätt att själv bestämma över sin kropp och sexuella umgänge. ”nu arbetar vi för att den generation som växer upp i dag aldrig ska behöva skriva #metoo”, skriver kristina henkel, @olikaforlag, emelie törnkvist, lorena tyréus, danielle berglund, helene andersson och annika nylén nilsson från maria förskolor i stockholm. på #allahjärtansdag = #samtyckesdagen.

text:
un mensaje de #sanvalentin 
el amor romántico mata
.
la idea de que una persona pertenece a otra, que los celos son amos, que los que se pelean se aman, la completa idealización de las personas, el amor a primera vista, todo esto es parte de lo que nos mata del amor romántico.

el amor es algo que se construye con las experiencias, no es algo que te apresa, la libertad de ser quien cada une es en la compañía y mutuo apoyó, eso es lo que consideró amor.
.
.

text:
нет сил писать какие-то глобальные посты, поэтому вот вам новость про американский исквайр (такой глянец модный мужской, есшо), фолловить тут - @esquire ⠀
⠀
темой февральского номера там стала жизнь белого, гетеросексуального парня, да ещё и цисгендера (гугол в помощь), представляете?! ⠀
⠀
речь в номере про то, как обычному белому американскому подростку живётся в эпоху #metoo, #этонеповодубить и прочих флешмобов в поддержку меньшинств. ⠀
⠀
и что вы думаете, исквайр таки обвинили в расизме! ну и правильно - кому нафиг нужна история про белых мальчиков в 2к19, их же уже столько было, пишет @huffpost. ⠀
⠀
а мне кажется, это интересная история, и я бы с радостью её почитал - так что если кто увидит американский журнал, привезите, а? ⠀
⠀

text:
.
putting this down in words was difficult.
and i hesitated before making it public.
.
but i felt that i had a duty to put this out here:
because there are few to no discussions about how victims recover from the trauma of sexual assault.
.
we expect it straightforward linear road to recovery,
and nobody talks about how that isn’t the case at all.
.
about how every step forward is accompanied by 4-5 steps backwards.
about how little things — sights, smells, even words — can paralyse you, often without warning.
about how no period of time seems long enough, or distance far enough, for us to leave it all behind.
.
about how you will always feel as if a part of you was violently torn away from you,
wondering if you will ever find yourself whole again.
.
.
.
.
.

.

text:
.
putting this down in words was difficult.
and i hesitated before making it public.
.
but i felt that i had a duty to put this out here:
because there are few to no discussions about how victims recover from the trauma of sexual assault.
.
we expect it straightforward linear road to recovery,
and nobody talks about how that isn’t the case at all.
.
about how every step forward is accompanied by 4-5 steps backwards.
about how little things — sights, smells, even words — can paralyse you, often without warning.
about how no period of time seems long enough, or distance far enough, for us to leave it all behind.
.
about how you will always feel as if a part of you was violently torn away from you,
wondering if you will ever find yourself whole again.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
know that there is help out there for anyone who has experienced sexual assault.

women's aid federation operate a 24/7 phone line, all details are below.

catherine ferrin from women's aid was kind enough to come into rehearsals last november to talk to our director and actors. she talked about the processes and help women's aid can provide for victims. she really helped us understand the themes we were undertaking.

there are still a few tickets available for our 2 performances in the american bar before we hit the road, taking wasted to school & community groups.

e-mail nuala@pintsizedni.com quoting either 3pm or 8pm and the no. of tickets you require.

we are kindly sponsored by the @departmentofjusticeni

text:
😍 good girls celebrate international women’s day| 08.03.19

the 8th march is international women’s day, so what better day to host a special gged event? come join us at the fabulous design museum, where we’ll be serving up searcys cuvee, delicious finger food and incredible speakers. 
tickets available from link in bio.

all guests are welcome to take a look around the permanent exhibition before moving to the kitchen where we’ll serve up delicious searcys food plus incredible speakers who’ll be giving their take on how much of their career, or life journey, was down to design - and how much was down to luck or judgement.

speakers:
dagmara kodlubanski - a director and filmmaker - currently completing her exciting film project, we still rise, in collaboration with passion pictures. we still rise is a feature length documentary about the women’s march that took place on january 21st 2017, the day after trump was inaugurated. it's a film that captures the moment the torch for #metoo was lit. (we’ll be screening a 4 minute trailer of the film on the night). 💥

the masons - maruska & donna-marie mason - are a london based photographer duo working across advertising, editorial and portraiture. inspired by people who break boundaries and are not afraid to lead the change, they explore diversity and equality in a timeless style with an edge, always pushing and allowing for their subject's personality and story to shine through. 📸 
lisa redman founded her own namesake label in 2007 having previously worked alongside betty jackson, elspeth gibson and as a textile designer for calvin klein. she now creates bespoke, contemporary womenswear with an expert team from her west london atelier. ⚡️ theme: luck, judgement or design

tickets available from link in bio
@searcyslondon @designmuseum @westillrisemovie @lisaredmanltd @themasonsofficial

text:
part. 3
"i need an anchor now, mama, to tell my stories.
but, mama with you i can’t have such conversations.
you allowed him to destroy your heart.
your heart has turned into a heart of glass.
i fear it will break if i told you these stories.
mama, can you handle it if i told you
what prostitution did to me in this big city?
if i told you your sweet little girl grew up to be a bitter child;
a bitter teenager, and a bitter woman?
mama, can you handle it if i told you the actual reason

why i ended up in a mental institution?
after the man whom i had a business deal with betrayed me,
i was devastated, mama.
he bought himself a brand new car
with the loan i borrowed from the bank.
instead of purchasing the stock we’d agreed on
he came back with a gorgeous yellow car from abroad.
i couldn’t believe my ears when i got his response.
he called me a ’slut’. nobody had ever called me that.
for a moment, i was lost.
i didn’t understand the purpose of this insult.
i was confused mama.
you know, ‘money is the root of all evil’;
i had never thought this saying was true until i experienced it." - lerato lehlabathe

you can now read her entire poem on our blog - http://wowement.blogg.se/

www.liferighting.com

#wowement #wmnpwr #survivors #endviolence #metoo #feminist #grlpwr

text:
💕 it’s valentine’s day 💕
and yea... i get to be a little bit smug. i get to take the hottest person i know on a date: me 😉
but... i’m going to be real with you. (cause i always fucking am)
i was a little bit needy towards one of my lovers yesterday when i was like “commee on!! it’s valentine’s day! you have to take me on a sexy date.” and he’s like “naah, i don’t hold much of valentine’s day, it’s a day supporting consumerism and sugar, both of which you hate btw.” and i was like “yesss but loveee!!! ♥️ love should be celebrated every day! however it makes me happy knowing we take one day to make an even bigger deal out of it!” but as he was saying it, i was secretly even happier, about him saying “no”, because i know that at all times i am in my highest experience. and my current mission and lessons all revolve around truly loving myself. and in order to get to that truly highest state of endless self orgasm, i need to experience a valentine’s day completely in my own flow. 
also, who this lover also has become to be in my life is my greatest mirror and teacher, living in an endless continuum of each others growth. 
so i knew to fully trust and allow myself to be in my full experience of self love. 
which means: for the first time in my life be totally and 100% delighted to be spending valentine’s day just me, without a date or an agenda. 
sometimes i feel like, especially us girls, we put valentine’s day on the calendar like: i better meet someone who is crazy about me by then! 
hahaha just writing it makes me laugh, but it’s so true! i’ve fallen victim to it so much, really wanting someone to validate me. telling me how beautiful, worthy, sexy, amazing, badass i am. 
like, if i am not witnessed by an other human (preferably an above average hot, smart, successful, sexy man) i don’t really exist or feel or ... count... how - does - that - make - any - fucking - sense? 
and we live our lives from this place of lack and need and forever wanting. 
naaahhhhh, that’s bullshit. i opt out, unsubscribe me from that spam ass newsletter.
hey, i’m raising my hand #metoo, #mefuckingtoo. 
i feel it, i see it, i know it.
i can different, you can different.
(rest 👇🏼)

text:
과연 #미투 #metoo 본질이 이게 맞나?
불륜을 왜 미투 사건으로 확대 시켰을까?
불륜을 저지른 #안희정 , #김지은 둘이서 가해자, 피해자 라고 말 하는걸까?
.
진짜 피해자는 안희정 측 가족들이 아닐까?
.
아마 미투 본질을 혐오를 조장하는 특정 집단 워xx , 메x ,김지은 , 언론 그리고 2심 재판부가 아닐까?
.
아직도 목소리도 못 내고 있는 미투 피해자들이 있다. 불륜 사건을 미투로 변화 시키면서  미투 운동 의미를 흐트려 놓지 말아야 한다.
여성, 남성 모두 사람으로서 인권 존중 받아야 한다.
.

.

.

.

text:
​​#историичитателей

не могу молчать! мне ужасно больно, больно не только душевно,но и физически! 
хочу рассказать, свою историю, чтоб девочки не совершали таких ошибок!

мне 26 (узбекская семья). познакомилась с мужчиной в интернете, начали общаться...красивые букеты, ухаживания ну просто идеальный мужчина, влюбилась.
случилось так, что попала к нему домой, и просто была там изнасилована (я была на тот момент девственницей) 😞  в результате чего разрывы, я до сих пор нахожусь на лечение, а он...он просто пропал. 
я осознаю, что сама виновата.

девочки будьте умнее, не совершайте ошибок.
=================

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text: "we must understand that there is no consent between powerful and powerless. we get a lot of teacher - student cases where teachers exploit the students and say that there was consent of the student involved. in many developed countries, such things are criminalized between teacher and student or between employer and employee. when a person feels disempowered, or respectful, or fearful of the other person, they smile. this smile does not mean consent. compliance doesn't mean consent. not resisting does not mean consent. going to your teacher's office is not consent. we must redefine consent." — #arfanamallah in session: redefining  consent: power, pleasure, patriarchy — 📸 @steermedia #lahootimelo #anodetowomen #metoo #ibelieveher #lahootimelo2019 #consent #lahooti #universityofsindh #qotd #futureisfemale

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
so many ‘teachers’ & facilitators in the neo-tantra & allied fields are encouraging & supporting people to feel more free & powerful in their sexuality, which is great, but, what i see after almost 10 years in that particular field is that almost no one is teaching people how to wield that power responsibly, it’s as if people forget the harm and damage an uncontrolled, unconscious & unmindful sexuality can have once they start to feel its power in a positive way.
.

text:
not the news i wanted to wake up to this morning, @ryanadams. i like to think i’m a believer in ‘innocent ‘til proven guilty’, but as a survivor of an emotionally abusive relationship; also with a charismatic, artistically-talented musician, who has since gone on to abuse other women; i can understand where these girls are coming from. if my ex were famous and people paid good money to go see him sing the songs he wrote about me, i’d be upset. it’s sad to think how the best art can come from the most troubled minds, but there’s never any excuse for emotional control - it’s so damaging, both at the time, and for all future relationships one tries to forge. i have tickets to the show in birmingham ryan, but i’m not sure i can go now. it’s a shame, but if those women have felt anything like the pain i went through, i have to stand by them 💔
.
.
.
#heartbroken #ryanadams #phoebebridgers #metoo #galentinesday

text:
søndagsevent 24/2 kl. 15:

journalist og forfatter anders haahr rasmussen synes, det er blevet svært at være mand. han savner et svar på, hvordan man bedst er mand i den 21. århundrede, og det leder han efter i sin nye bog, “en fandens mand”. “når haahr skriver om fordomme, om sexisme, om grænsen mellem det spontane og det krænkende, tror jeg, at mange – måske særligt unge mænd – vil føle sig både truffet og set – og måske få trang til at springe ind i en samtale, der kan flytte noget,” skriver informations anmelder.

gennem en blanding af personlige historier, essays og interviews fortæller anders haahr om at date, om #metoo, om grænser, om sexisme og homofobi, en hel del om sex og særligt om, hvordan mænd kan finde sig til rette på en bane, hvor spillereglerne ikke er helt de samme, som de var for tyve år siden. det handler om de store spørgsmål: hvorfor er det så svært at være mand over for en kvinde? hvad skal der til for at det bliver sjovere, friere, mere livsbekræftende?

forfatteren bliver interviewet af journalist og boghandler rikke viemose.

entré: 60,- (50,- for medlemmer). hvis du vil være sikker på at få en plads, kan du tilmelde dig ved at sende en mail til til@thiemersmagasin.dk

for teaching us how to listen and for her work ending the suffering in silence, this #blackhistorymonth we honor @taranajaneen
.

text:
aviation: holding you, i held everything (9/10) by nicholas jones, 19 january 2019. -

i can’t think about what could have been when you’re no longer here,
and as i try to put the words together - they begin to disappear,
because it’s just too hard to accept the fact that i will never hear,
you sing along whenever your favorite song comes on,
ever again,

i can’t think about the passenger side - windows rolled down,
and your hair being tossed in the wind,
or the way your smile could outshine,
the sun in the middle of a cool summer day,
by the pool,

it’s only been a couple of weeks and i can’t tell you what hurts more,
seeing you in my dreams and knowing this is all we’ll ever be,
or living through each day looking for you in every person that i see,
wondering if i will ever be able to find my soul in someone else,
ever again,

regardless of how much time has passed,
i still think of you and me all of the time - especially at night,
when shooting stars cross paths to the rhythm of steel guitars,
because when i was holding you - i held everything,
i always needed. -

text:
separation between mind and body
this is how trauma after the incident remains in the body. the mind tries to rationalize what happened while the body holds tension of what actually happened
h e a l i n g - when a trigger thought shows up, observe if it originates in the mind or body. breathe into it. deep breathe into your belly and then your chest, hold, and release the breath slowly. allow the movements your body needs as you repeat the breathing. allow the thought to float way.
#journeytolight
📸: @hafsahmalik14

.

text:
hollywood’s hijack of the #metoo movement
#
| posted: feb 14, 2019 12:01 am the opinions expressed by columnists are their own and do not represent the views of townhall.com. the powerful #metoo movement was established to address real injustices suffered by women -- and in some cases, although significantly less common, by men. this movement has undeniably affected societal norms and readjusted the fabric of american life.but such an important movement can be felled by its own excesses. in the wake of the #metoo movement, people are immediately rushing to judgment and to punishment of any accused individual -- in many cases, without due process. naturally, this moblike mentality to blindly punish an accused individual has the potential for far-reaching negative consequences -- namely, collateral damage to the falsely accused by those who misuse the movement for their own ambitious aims.take, for example, the domestic abuse allegations against johnny depp, which should serve as a cautionary tale. depp is a beloved actor who has won a 14 people's choice awards. he is, by all accounts, a serial monogamist. his first wife and three decades' worth of long-term girlfriends uniformly characterize him as a sensitive and caring partner.and then he met and married amber heard, who has made…

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
how amazon’s ‘the boys’ will handle the bawdy in the current #metoo era – tca
##metoo #amazon #breaking news #evan goldberg #seth rogen #tca #the boys
in garth ennis’ comic book series the boys, there’s some really risque events involving women that goes down, scenes in this #metoo era which would be hard to argue as apropos. in what sounds like a similar dystopian world that dc’s watchmen would dwell in, the boys takes place during a time when superheros have an american idol-type of mass appeal, however, they’re awful people and abuse women, and abuse power to a great degree. hughie (jack quaid) suffers a great loss at the hands of a reckless ‘supe’, and his devastation turns to outrage when there’s no legal recourse for those who are victims of collateral superhero damage. hugie meets billy butcher, (karl urban), a mysterious operative who recruits him to pursue vigilante justice against the ‘supes’. in regards to handling such lewd moments from the comic-book, the boys showrunner/ep eric kripke said at amazon’s tca today, that such shocking creative choices only make sense if it furthers the character. “if something doesn’t further the character, we cut it,” said the supernatural creator, “then the irreverence wouldn’t be for shock value.” like ennis’ preacher which is heading into its fourth season from the boys eps seth rogen and evan goldberg, the latest amazon superhero series is meant to push boundaries. erin moriarty who plays starlight/annie january on the show is in some of these bawdy scenes. the reason why she felt strongly why “the hard and ugly stuff” should be put in the show is “because it’s happening, and we need to talk about it….it’s a commentary of what’s going on now.” “as long we don’t treat it as a f***king joke,” said kripke about the series approach to its controversial scenes, “if it’s real and happening to these characters; their actions and ramifications, we give (the content) the gravity it deserves.”

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
this week, my family dealt with an extremely stressful and traumatic issue that i can't discuss for legal reasons. 
yesterday we spent the whole day in a small room with 10 women and my beautiful, supportive, gentle and strong husband.
we experienced tears, laughter, long silences, meditation, shared food, frightened moments and more tears. 
there are many things that i'm trying to process from yesterday and will one day write about. however what is strong in my heart today is the power of the women (and one man) in that room, who ranged 5 decades and came together to carry each other through a highly emotive experience. 
i put on a strong face, when inside i was utterly terrified. but my family and friends gave me strength and i'll be forever grateful. 
i wish we didn't have to endure that experience, but we so lucky to have been surrounded by generous, loving souls. 
#womensupportingwomen #family #justice #truthcomesout #womenempowerment #metoo #timesup #chasingenso #rewriteyourstory #writewhatyoufeel #writer #myvillage #smallvictories

text:
the 2019 women's follows the 2017 women's march and 2018 women's march. in early 2017, during the aftermath of president trump's election, around four million people gathered in washington dc for the first women's march, a protest against legislation and rhetoric that harms women. however, news reports from across north america noted that turnout for the 2019 women's march was lower compared to previous years, with potential reasons being poor weather, a decline in interest and controversy over protest organization in the united states.
(photo by daniel rad)

text:
perspective. one of the key concepts to keep in mind when mingling with others throughout your day. understanding that the lens you see through is what creates your reality. understanding that there is no select number of lens in the world, is important. everyone is different and different upbringings, history, experiences, relationships, environment and more all shape how we are and process things. be kind to your neighbors. be kind to those who may not get it. be kind to those who were raised differently than you. be kind to those who look different than you, speak differently than you, and think differently than you.
.
stunning image 📸: via @vocal_creators 🎶
.
.
.
