text:
my face washed away today when i received the call from my dad asking, “is the trial date still set to march 11, 2019?” me: yes as far as i know no one has called me and said anything differently. father: “well i just heard that he was freed of all charges. me: my heart stop instantly. i immediately call the district attorneys only to get no response to find out that this matter was true. i did everything by the books of the law and they failed me tremendously. after being raped i went to emergency room and had s.a.n.e. kit done. re-living the story daily to get justice. i kept clothes that i had on the day i was raped. a no contact order was placed for my protection or at least i thought. until one day i saw my rapist, i did as i was instructed call the brandon police dept. if he didn’t voluntarily remove himself. well he didn’t. it took 11 accuracies for us to get a court date of this matter. to only be told the no contact paper that was signed meant if he was in my reach he would be arrested and held in jail until trial. well after 11 accuracies he didn’t go to jail, i had witnesses of the matter and the judge whitney only gave him 24 months probation. i have been lied to by the rankin co. system since day one. i’ve asked for anyone to help guide me for i saw things not making sense. so just when i left the decision/trust in the hands of the law they failed me. november 7, 2017 i was raped by corey armond beard. to find out today on february 13, 2019 through word of month he was freed blew my mind. did he pay someone to get him off, or did the system just fail me. i was told by da’s office jessica you are strong one and i know you can/will get through this. however how do you know that i will, i was raped and with all evidence on the table you let him walk. i want justice, & need your help to know what to do when the law fails you...was my skin to dark was this a racial act that i wasn’t protected? 
myo~voice .
.
.
.

text:
i live my life through a small window pane. i pretend no one can see me. no one knows my name. i cry when it rains to hide the tears. i pretend to enjoy life when others are near. who am i to think i deserve to be loved...to be wanted...to be needed...to be kissed...to be hugged? i used to see their faces when i closed my eyes. i used to hate living...i wanted to die. why didn't i find the courage to speak? why did those things keep happening to me? over and over even when i said no...the monsters kept coming...they wouldn't let go. maya angelou became a mute. i wish i did the same thing too. i live my life through a small window pane. i pretended no one could see me. no one knew my name. i still cry when it rains to hide my tears. i still pretend to enjoy life when others are near. guilt consumes my thoughts at times...but i'm so tired of the darkness, i accept the sunshine.
#metoo #survivor #speakup #yourvoicehaspower #youmatter #findthesunshine #endthesilence

text:
representation is so important. @odaatnetflix is the first show about a latinx family that i can relate to and season 3 took it to a whole other level with addressing #metoo. it portrayed the conversation through a multi-generational lense, using affirmative consent education, and storytelling. this episode and this entire show is so powerful. we need these stories, now, more than ever and we need them told by latinx folks. a huge thank you to the women who made this show happen and are telling our stories in a beautiful and comedic way. 
so friends, grab a cafecito, and start watching because you won’t be disappointed. #dale 💃🏻

text:
today i sat for almost 12 hours listening to testimony at the first #sexualharassment hearings in albany in 27 years.

there are so many way that victims of abuse and harassment cannot get justice for what happened to them, whether they report or not.

i came to honor their pain, show that we believe victims and because there have been moments where i have made others uncomfortable and i could not hold myself with integrity if i'm not taking responsibility and hearing from others on how to be better.

#albany #maleprivilege #metoo

text: last year it was #metoo and now this year it is the black face discussion... recently old photos of politicians and detectives in blackface has caused quite the media storm. nick cannon resurfaced jimmy kimmel and jimmy fallon in blackface in a comedy sketch. years ago jaime foxx had remarks for robert downey jr for his blackface portrayal in the movie. let’s not forget shawn and marlon wayans doing whiteface in a movie as well as eddie murphy in an snl sketch and they were many more examples. blackface became popular with thomas rice’s jump jim crow. blackface has caused a lot of trouble with pain and sorrow and still to this day the same eerie reminders still linger. 1/3 of a recent pol say nothing is wrong with it on halloween. if white people can’t do blackface then should black people be able to do whiteface? if it’s in a comedy routine and clearly in the context of comedy then is that ok? does doing blackface automatically make you a racist? are we going to start lumping everyone in the same category as many do the same way with the metoo movement? #blackface #whiteface

text:
thanks for this reminder about consent @thesweetfeminist ! springing a kiss on someone isn’t consent. don’t lean in 100%. it’s always better to ask. there are a lot of ways to ask. “want to kiss me?” “can i kiss you?” “your lips are looking mighty kissable today...” sometimes a person may not want to kiss (for a million reasons or for no reason at all) & we must have respect for that no (direct - “i’m not feeling it” or indirect - “i’m super tired”) and deal with any feels that are coming up from rejection elsewhere. happy valentine’s day. practice consent always! 🥰💓🌿✨
.
.
.

text:
[cw: paedophilia, abuse] 
i have cried plenty of cathartic tears to your songs, @ryanadams, but tonight i am crying because you let me down.

when i was fourteen years old, my friend and his dad took me to your show in cardiff and it lit a fire inside me. until a few hours ago, you were one of my favourite artists. 
you, who inspired me to write and sing and play and be sad and loud and weird and proud, have proven yourself more of a disappointment than you could ever know.

for anyone reading this who hasn't had the misfortune of reading the new york times article yet, mister adams has been exposed for his three thousand explicit texts from his forty year old self to an underage girl, and a stream of women have come forward about his emotionally manipulative and abusive tendancies.

ryan, for my entire adult life, your songs have been my first choice for comfort when i have had to indulge in the beautiful pain of heartbreak. i honestly thought i would be a lifelong fan.

i hope you lose everything. with due respect to the other artists on pax-am, i hope that one day you learn of the forced sale of your label from a news reporter on a blurry screen in the dining hall of the grottiest prison new york has to offer.

i want you to know how deeply and bitterly you have disappointed someone who admired you.

in what was once my favourite song, you told me that you taught yourself how to grow old.

teach yourself how to grow the fuck up. 🖕

#ryanadams #burnyourryanadamsrecords #paxam #metoo #dontsupportabusers

text:
the saddest thing i was told last year by a loved one was “me too.” sadness was not the only emotion i felt. a barrage of emotions flooded over me, and i wished i could have been there to protect them. though so many years have gone by, some of the hurt still remains not just from the abuse but from the ridicule they experienced when they went to other family members for help. the abuser no longer in the land of the living.  no justice, no peace? no, not so! this became their song in the night. “when peace, like a river, attendeth my way, 
when sorrows like sea billows roll; 
whatever my lot, thou hast taught me to say, 
it is well, it is well with my soul.”
#metoo #itiswell #itiswell #withher #healherolord #makeherwholeagain

text:
some may say i am too much.
some may say i am not enough.
but i choose to love myself exactly as i am.

i am a soulful, rich, deep, embodied, heartfelt woman.
and i am not backing down.

i believe in myself and i want every woman in the world to believe in herself, too.

we had #metoo and we called it out.
now it's our time to do the inner work.
we are worthy. we are beautiful. 
we are powerful.
it's time to transform ourselves so we can transform this situation.

i will raise my voice. i will speak my truth. 
i will shine my light. i will be true to myself.
i declare i am finished giving my power away to anyone.
i am free! 💚

text:
es #sanvalentin o el día de los #enamorados. yo creo ciegamente en el amor, porque el amor es un gesto transformador. y aunque esté hoy sola porque mi ex me dejó hace unas semanas: voy a pedir a san valentín por derechos porque la gente se ame libremente y sin violencia real ni símbolica, porque en los vínculos se diga la verdad y no se engañe, porque se cuiden unos a otros, porque sientan felicidad y deseo por encontrarse, porque se entreguen sin miedo al amor. también quiero pedir porque los hombres nos dejen de mirar como putas, se va caer el patriarcado queridos porque lo vamos hacer caer. también quiero pedir porque la mirada no discrimine más la diversidad de vínculos, yo también como vos tuve un primo que se murió por no poder amar a los de su mismo sexo. también quiero pedir san valentín las mujeres seamos libres de disponer de nuestros cuerpos, no se pude tener un hijo sin desearlo, con alguien que no te ama, yo también tuve una prima se murió por un aborto clandestino, que sea legal y gratuito. yo quiero que en todas las combinaciones posibles los cuerpos se iluminen de amor. yo amo y ame profundamente y es la sensación mas liberadora que experimenta el cuerpo y el espíritu, doy fé.

text:
healthy relationships feel good! 
this valentines day, we wish you all the love! 
february is a time to celebrate all the love, and it is also teen dating action month. there is a special hotline devoted to supporting teens called loveisrespect. you or your teen can reach out by calling 1-866-331-9474, texting loveis to 22522, or chatting online at loveisrespect.org.
want more valentine love? copy and paste this link into your browser. 
https://wscadv.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/valentine-cards.pdf and check hashtags #tdvam2019 #huddleup #tdvam to link to the national effort!

text: entry 1: november 18th  it’s february 13th, 2019 - roughly 2:00pm. instead of working, i’m currently sitting alone in a room at the er. i’m in cat hair covered leggings, my college hoodie, hair still wet from my shower, and the socks my mom got me after watching happy feet - “so you can be happy when you wear them” she told me. i purposely wore them so i could look down at my feet and smile. today, i had to say more than just “it happened again” - the phrase i had come to use over the past couple of days as my shock gave way into reality and i confided in friends and family. today i had to verbally say what “it” was that happened. i have been denying “it” for so long, the words seemed to be in a foreign language. i felt my mouth move, but i could barely register what i was saying - “i’m here for a sexual assault exam” i tell the nurse. • read the full blog post by clicking on the link in my bio •

text:
“this is how we’ve always done it.”
.
let's cut right to the chase!  from know your rights, which opened today!! (link in profile):
.
surprisingly, tradition is a major driver in maternity care!  healthcare is very slow to change—and maternity care is particularly slow to change.  it takes years and years for research to be implemented into practice, and attitudes about our agency in birth are just as slow.  the way our rights are treated in childbirth lag far behind advances made in our rights in other areas.
.
.
.
paternalism is “the policy or practice on the part of people in positions of authority of restricting the freedom and responsibilities of those subordinate to them in the subordinates’ supposed best interest.” in maternity care, paternalism is rampant. consider the phrasing “not allowed” or “won’t let” in reference to maternity care. you’ve probably used or heard these phrases used—they are so common, in fact, they’re often used by the media.
.

text:
about the book 
in the woman in the mirror, author evelyn mejil provides a vivid portrait of her courageous mind meeting her painful memories, her valiant heart overcoming her shameful unworthiness, and her bold spirit overpowering her relentless fear.
in this account, mejil shares an uncensored description of how she overcomes her past when she discovers an inconspicuous truth while traveling the world in search for answers to silence her nightmares and heal her pain. hidden in the eyes of the woman reflected in the mirror, she sees the answers stood where she buried her painful past, and to find them there is only one journey left to take, a journey within.
the woman in the mirror tells how once she goes beyond the memories and faces her demons, she finally discovers her true being and vividly recounts how her false self, the identity birthed in the lies of her past, collapses. shattering the iron grip of her past, she heals and brings forth a new story. mejil presents the unadulterated expression of her most powerful self, the authentic self.
order your copy today by visiting: evelynmejil.com link in bio 🔝

text: it’s time we normalize talk about sex with our kids and engage in age specific talks about intimacy. in the netherlands they start at 4 years old. what do they have to show for being so progressive? a smaller orgasm gap, less sexual assault, less unwanted pregnancy and less stds. we need to decrease the disparity between boys and girls in regards to sexual pleasure. our girls should engage in sexual practices responsibly with a focus on their pleasure. their pleasure should not predominately be based on making a boy reach orgasm. let’s change the culture of sexuality and raise boys and girls who engage in a mutually enjoyable, respectful, and responsible sexual relationships. #letstalkaboutsex #letstalkaboutyouandme #sexed #sexeducation #relationshiptherapy #sexualeducation #metoo #timesup #knowledgeispower #lovenotfear #nobettertimethantoday #sowhatisaidorgasm #orgasm #omgyes.com #forherpleasure #feminist #feminism #feministmemes

text:
how trauma impacts your body. often, when someone survives a traumatic incident — such as a sexual assault, police brutality, a hate crime, or a school shooting — the trauma stays with them, even though the danger is gone.

if trauma is left untreated, it can impact your physical health. in other words, if you’ve survived a traumatic incident, ignoring mental health treatment can negatively impact your body. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/02/13/how-trauma-impacts-your-body/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #dissociativeidentitydisorder #trauma #therapydog #doitfordolly

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
the world’s longest running south asian film festival outside india, uk asian film festival, announces ‘revolution’ theme for 2019.⁣⁣ at a time of significant change, the world’s longest running south asian film festival outside india marks its 21st anniversary with a curation inspired by the theme of revolution. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
honouring ‘revolution’ through the vehicle of south asian cinema, uk asian film festival looks at the #metoo movement gathering momentum in the indian and pakistani film industries and the decriminalisation of homosexuality and the repeal of section 377 in india last year.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
2. ek aasha (a hope) (2018, dir. mayur katariya)⁣⁣⁣⁣
3. evening shadows (2018, dir. sridhar rangayan)⁣⁣⁣⁣
4. bengali film chegu (2018, dir. nabamita ghosh)⁣⁣⁣⁣
5. noblemen (2019, dir. vandana kataria)⁣⁣⁣⁣
6. the opening film is india’s youngest oscar-nominated and two-time national award-winning filmmaker ashvin kumar’s no fathers in kashmir (2017). the screening will be followed by a q&a with director ashvin kumar and actress soni razdan. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
7. one of the most celebrated masterpieces of indian cinema, pakeezah (1972, dir. kamal amrohi), will be screened at the british library on monday 1st april followed by a q&a with tajdar kamal amrohi, director, producer, writer and son of the late, legendary pakeezah filmmaker kamal amrohi. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
8. provoked (2006, dir. jag mundhra) with a q&a with kiranjit ahluwalia.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
9. burning an illusion (1981, dir. menelik shabazz) on saturday 30th march, rich mix. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
10. followed by my beautiful launderette (1981, dir. stephen frears).⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
11. brick lane (2007, dir. sarah gavron) on saturday 6th april, rich mix. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
festival dates: ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
london: 27th march – 7th april⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
edinburgh: 29th march – 31st march⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
leicester: 4th april – 7th april⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
manchester: 30th april – 4th may⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
full festival programme will be announced on 27th february 2019.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

text: be still my heart. a few months ago i read about this woman’s project wherein she asked for women to send in their purity rings, which she would melt down into a feminist sculpture. she also sent a certificate and a “replacement” shameless ring as a thank you. i mailed in both of mine. today i got to see the outcome, and she even noted my story in the article. http://huffp.st/titexpb  this is obviously the most personal and direct of my social media posts, which is terrifying but shouldn’t be. so proud and honored to be part of this and living #shameless in our #metoo era. #nadiabolzweber @sarcasticlutheran @gloriasteinem

text:
"dare i disturb the universe?" the concept or luck or fortune as an arbitrary force that controls our lives is often personified as a woman. the roman godess fortuna was thought to dole out good or bad luck with the turn of her wheel. free will or choice is recognized as a means of circumventing luck, or using it to one's advantage. however, women themselves who make choices are often vilified. for eating from the tree of knowledge, the biblical eve is remembered as the corruptor of divine creation. today, women in many parts of the world are discouraged or prevented from making choices about their bodies, their educations, their marriages.  here, i reinterpret the fruit as a symbol of humanity's first free act. a female figure evades fortuna and prepares to make a choice. in doing so, she may disturb the universe, but she understands that in a world so often governed by circumstance, choices are rare and precious things. .
.
.
#linocut #blockprinting #art #artistsofinstagram #artofinstagram #empowerment
#feminism #choice #metoo

text:
in the ‘year of the woman,’ many were missing from international reporting

journalism around the world remains dominated by male reporters and their male sources. but that’s starting to change. .
.
unless you avoided the internet entirely last year, you probably saw almost every major publicationdeclare 2018 “the year of the woman.”
in the united states, christine blasey ford accused the then–supreme court nominee brett kavanaugh of sexual assault. two months later, a record number of women were elected to congress. the #metoo movement gained steam and sexual-misconduct bombshells rockednearly every industry, across the globe. people seemed to finally be paying attention to women’s voices.

those voices weren’t, however, often included in reported stories. journalism remains dominated by male reporters and their male sources. a study published recently by the women’s media center found that in 2017, 63 percent of bylines and tv credits were those of men. the imbalance is even more pronounced when it comes to international reporting, with men producing two-thirds of the stories in that field. globally, only 24 percent of news subjects (including people who are interviewed and those whom a story is about) are women, according to a 2015 study. (the atlantic’s global section fared only marginally better in 2018, with women constituting 27 percent of those quoted. forty-one percent of people who wrote for the global section were women.)
name: feminin in society

those voices weren’t, however, often included in reported stories. journalism remains dominated by male reporters and their male sources. a study published recently by the women’s media center found that in 2017, 63 percent of bylines and tv credits were those of men. the imbalance is even more pronounced when it comes to international reporting, with men producing two-thirds of the stories in that field. globally, only 24 percent of news subjects (including people who are interviewed and those whom a story is about) are women, according to a 2015 study. (the atlantic’s global section fared only marginally better in 2018, with women constituting 27 percent of those quoted. forty-one percent of people who wrote for the global section were women.)

text:
this year i want: renewal 🌼
"the focus of my story is not on past trauma—it is on everything that i am in spite of that: resilient, strong, courageous, brave, valuable, loved, and whole.  for too long i’ve let myself be shrouded in shame, afraid of what the imperfections and the challenges i have faced in life say about me.  the reality is that i can be broken, but i cannot be destroyed. bravely confronting the dark and rejecting false responsibility is how i create space for my personal healing and growth. renewal is my battle cry.

this year, i am becoming what i already am but sometimes fail to see. i am extending myself the love that i give to others. renewal is the revitalization of myself and my life after the last year. it is a renewal of how i view and treat myself, a renewal of my faith, a renewal of my freedom, my power, and my courage. the villain in my story was not anyone or anything that brought me pain, it was my belief in the lie that anything or anyone could make me less than who i am.” -blackblessedblog (see the full story on our blog).

text:
👋 hi there, long time no post. i’ve been on a social media hiatus. i probably will take another insta break after this post, but wanted to update. pictured above: pieces from a journal prompt that i used to distract myself when i was having a hard time with trauma stuff. my time in africa was unlike any other and i so often miss the simplicity of the lifestyle and genuine relationships with others. 💗 ———————————————————————————grateful for: 🌱date with my hubby on friday 🌱 awesome coworkers 🌱 coffee 🌱 my kids 🌱 that i’m able to afford trauma treatment 🌱 i’ve been more self compassionate lately 🙌
———————————————————
emdr update: i was able to get an appt with my #emdrtherapist this week. i didn’t think i would get in again until 2/20/19. during session i was prompted to visualize the most intense part of the rape in my mind and we worked to pair it with the negative thought that comes to mind. mine was, “i am disgusting.” then had to brainstorm a positive thought i want to replace it with, “i am whole.” next session we will visualize a safe place and do work around that and then it is time for actual emdr. i’m excited and nervous. therapy was last night and definitely uncontained today, but handling it as well as i can. just super exhausted this week and so that is tough. i’m looking forward to a long weekend and an early bedtime tonight. sending lots of love your way, and if you’re struggling... i see you, you matter, and you got this!! 💗💗💗

text:
-trauma informed care-  in the u.s, one in three women experience some form of sexual violence in their lifetime, and the incidences are even higher for lgbtq individuals. for individuals who have experienced this type of trauma, going for a gyne exam or dealing with a pregnancy can be a potentially triggering experience. midwives have a unique opportunity to provide a safe, respectful space to provide necessary care without causing additional harm. this is called trauma-informed care, and it’s something all clinicians should be providing to all individuals, regardless of a known history of trauma. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
some of the ways the omg midwives provide trauma informed care include:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* screening for previous sexual trauma during visits and on our intake forms⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* starting the visit with our client fully clothed⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* determining first if a pelvic exam is even necessary or beneficial. we decide together if that is the right time for a pelvic exam ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* if our client consents to a pelvic exam, we offer a chaperone :an additional support person to be present during the exam⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* before starting an exam, we receive consent again, and give our client the power to stop the exam at any point⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* we offer and support speculum self insertion, and use the smallest possible speculum with lubricant⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* we can complete the exam without the use of stirrups. instead, our client’s legs are on the table, which is more comfortable and less exposed. they also have more control of their body and can reposition or move away as needed. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* we avoid using triggering language during our exams, and pay close attention to our client’s body language. if there is any feedback that portrays non-consent,  the exam is stopped.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
* this also applies in the context of pregnancy, with cervical exams: determining a need, receiving consent, ability to withdrawal consent at anytime, and making the exam as comfortable as possible. #traumainformedcare #survivor #lgbtq #healthycervix #thisiswhatmidwiferylookslike  #informedconsent  #metoo
name: AMITA OMG Women’s Healthcare

text:
for nearly two decades, ryan adams, one of the most prolific singer-songwriters of his generation, has been heralded as a mercurial creative genius and a respected industry tastemaker.

he has also taken a special interest in the trajectory of female artists, especially younger ones, championing them onstage, across social media and in the studio, where his stamp of approval can jump-start careers.

some now say that adams’s rock-star patronage masked a darker reality. in interviews, seven women and more than a dozen associates described a pattern of manipulative behavior in which adams dangled career opportunities while simultaneously pursuing female artists for sex. in some cases, they said, he would turn domineering and vengeful, jerking away his offers of support when spurned, and subjecting women to emotional and verbal abuse, and harassment in texts and on social media. the accounts have been corroborated by family members or friends who were present at the time, as well as by correspondence from adams reviewed by the new york times.
_____
story: @nytimes | photos: douglas gorenstein/nbc, via getty images and elizabeth weinberg for the @nytimes | @ryanadams #ryanadams @mandymooremm #mandymoore #metoo #metoomovement

he has also taken a special interest in the trajectory of female aists, especially younger ones, championing them onstage, across social media and in the studio, where his stamp of approval can jump-sta careers.

some now say that adams’s rock-star patronage masked a darker reality. in interviews, seven women and more than a dozen associates described a pattern of manipulative behavior in which adams dangled career oppounities while simultaneously pursuing female aists for sex. in some cases, they said, he would turn domineering and vengeful, jerking away his offers of suppo when spurned, and subjecting women to emotional and verbal abuse, and harassment in texts and on social media. the accounts have been corroborated by family members or friends who were present at the time, as well as by correspondence from adams reviewed by the new york times.

text:
according to multiple sources, president donald trump is expected to sign and pass the proposed spending bill by congress in the coming days to avoid another government shutdown. although this is really only speculation, information from some of trumps aides (who have chosen to remain anonymous) indicates he will pass this spending bill. trump has indicated that he would “definitely like to avoid” another shutdown. however, the spending bill only guarantees 1.38 billion dollars of the 5.7 billion dollars trump and the department of homeland security had asked for for border security and wall funding. these same sources also indicate that trump is prepared to take 900 million dollars worth of additional funds that is available to the executive branch for construction projects, which would bring the number up to 2.3 billion. some then speculate that he may direct billions of dollars of funds from other areas or declare a national emergency in order to fund the rest of the border security that he and the dhs had deemed necessary. 
____________________________________________________

text:
💄💄💄
@sandradewey and i created feminist friday in summer 2017 as an opportunity to informally connect with other turner women in la. as the #timesup and #metoo movements gained momentum later that year, it became clear that we needed to solidify this safe space.
💖💖💖
since then, we’ve grown to include a breakfast series, screenings, self-defense classes, fundraisers, and more! today’s 2019 kickoff in celebration of galentine’s day was the first time we opened up the group to the men in the company (hi, allies!), and i’m so excited to watch us flourish this year! well done ladies! 💐
ps: happy black history month! who knows where my pin is from? ✊🏾🤔
#la #wcw #feminist #girlpower #blackgirlmagic

text:
join the #justice4gemmel coalition, #metoo international la and myself as we stand with male survivors of sexual harassment, sexual violence and exploitation! break the silence around male victims! arrest ed buck and demand justice for gemmel moore and timothy dean!

in light of recent allegations of sexual misconduct within gay men's chorus la (gmcla) involving artistic director jonathan weedman and west hollywood mayor john duran, we are announcing a press conference and peaceful rally to address a broader culture of complicity within west hollywood. 
for many of us who have respect for john duran's long legacy as a defender of lgbtq civil liberties, we are disheartened to see his contributions dampened by alleged behavior. 
meanwhile, the fight for justice for all victims of ed buck continues. the proximity of democratic leadership (including john duran) to prominent democratic donor- and alleged serial killer- ed buck is of concern to us all. 
we heal when we demand accountability from our own. city officials, commissioners and weho residents are invited to reaffirm our communities' solidarity with male survivors.

join us to make an intentional shift in tone in our community and say male survivors matter! align with justice for gemmel moore and timothy dean, and all survivors of ed buck!

our demands: 
1. arrest ed buck! end complicity by west hollywood city in the sexual predation of black queer men, sex workers, and people in survival economies in our community! john duran speak up about the crisis in your own west hollywood! 
2. demand accountability of gmcla creative director jonathan weedman and west hollywood mayor john duran! until results of a thorough, unbias investigation are complete, 
duran step down from city council! weedman step down from gmcla!

3. improved protocols throughout all city systems to build competency, and affirm the validity of male survivors of sexual harassment, sexual violence or exploitation. 
4. full transparency in city and gmcla finances in proximity to sexual misconduct allegations to rule out that revenues were not misused, endangering gmcla's organizational stability and the credibility of city of west hollywood

text:
practicing the left hand of “everything’s fucked”. a song i wrote almost immediately after the orange man got elected south of the boarder. i played the song at 2 gigs after that, and then got really depressed and didn’t play any shows until like now.. anyone else got a little more depressed after trump got elected? watching all the human rights violations and spread of hate and fear of other people? it’s like it kind of killed my hope in humanity... but seeing the people in the local communities fight and make strides gave me hope, like the women’s march, or how over 100 diverse women got elected into u.s. politics in 2018!

text:
a part of me..
you may never see.
you may never know.
you may never understand.
i am a representative for women and girls in economics , technology, sports, security, health care, education, politics, and above all development. 
i am part of the revolution. 
i am a bad feminist.
my place at the table is to protect all the rights of women and girls. 
and prove to the world; we are brighter, stronger, resilient, powerful and brave. 
we can reach the peak of our careers while keeping a home. 
we can be single mothers. 
we can be women with disabilities. 
we can be into entertainment and not prostitutes. 
we might have infertility issues due to health issues not abortion or uninformed assumptions. 
we can be bosses without using our bodies. 
we can be single on our own terms. 
we can be divorced not because we can’t keep a home or we are too unruly. 
we might have mood swings but capable of leadership. 
we might be flashy but less demanding. 
we are capable of doing better than our past. 
our dress code is no indication of our personality. 
our #metoo stories are true and projects how rape culture threatens us daily. 
i am a woman that pledges to support, empower and mentor my kind. 
i am a woman 
you may never see. 
never know. 
never understand. 
#woman #empowerment #politics #womeninsuits #pcos #entertainment #economics #womeninsports #womeninfilm #womeninpower #womensupportwomen #education #nigeriadecides2019 #nigeriadecides #

text:
lisa flotlin, 29, was sexually assaulted by her high school spanish teacher when she was 17. eight years later, at 25, she realized she wanted to press charges but, due to convoluted statute of limitations laws, found out that she no longer had the option to seek justice. she is now sharing her story to help prompt changes to statute of limitations laws, including simplifying and extending the reporting period. photo by @gmartphoto.
#metoo #seattle #waleg #sexualassault

text:
💗 with valentine’s day in full swing, it’s a good time to take a look at office romances and the steps employers should take to ensure they don’t get caught up in the #metoo maelstrom.⠀
.⠀
📱 in an age of online romance and “hook up culture”, it might be surprising to learn that meeting a partner in the workplace remains one of the most common ways to find romance. in a 2018 survey by us careers website vault.com, 52% of surveyed workers reported having had some kind of romantic involvement with a co-worker, with more than half of those relationships being described as more serious than a “random hook up”.⠀
.⠀
🤔 while it remains commonplace, has the #metoo era dimmed the enthusiasm of workers for workplace romance? the data would seem to suggest that this is the case. more than a quarter of the vault.com respondents reported that #metoo era allegations of sexual harassment against prominent men have made them less likely to think that romantic relationships between colleagues are acceptable.⠀
.⠀
👀 read the full article. link in bio! ⠀
.⠀

text:
jealousy

this is a song that talks about a real problem in our brain when we start to create a "jealousy" crisis because we feel insecure for so many reasons. it could be because of your own fears or because the other person maybe doesn't really take care of you and for that reason you start feeling alone and not really happy. it is in this moment when you start to feel that everything goes wrong, and you can't see the way out... you just wanna kill someone! then we are scared of ourselves! that's kill us! 😟😬😵 it is a bad feeling that finally destroys yourself and everything around you. also it makes you feel that your are losing your energy putting every little piece of your heart into a hard situation making you suffer a lot of anger. so, let's kick this feeling out and far away from us!!!
breathe and search for real love. ❤️❤️❤️
if you wanna listen the complete song, follow me on @spotify & @deezer and with lyrics, on youtube. 😘😘 🌹🌹🌹🌹
😍😍🌷🌺💐🌸🌸🌻🌻
esta es una canción que habla de un problema real que se genera en tu cerebro cuando se crea una crisis de celos. puede estar desencadenada por una suma de miedos e inseguridades propias que ya arrastrábamos desde hace mucho tiempo, o bien también por el hecho de sentimos bastante desprotegidos por la otra persona que se supose que "te quiere". 😆"jeaulosy" habla de ese momento en el que te das terror de vos misma, cuando ya llegás al límite y no ves la luz a través del tunel, teniendo ganas de matar a alguien de tanta mala energia que se acumula por tanto lidiar con todos esos malos pensamientos y sensaciones. eso mata! 
por eso, vamos a patear el tablero dejando esos sentimientos fuera y lejos nuestro!!!
respiremos y busquemos amor verdadero. ❤️ para escuchar la versión completa, siganme en @spotify y @deezer!

williams turned himself in to authorities.

text:
tendencias, diseñadores, exclusividad, lujo... creo que son algunas de las palabras que cruzan en la mente al pensar sobre el concepto de moda, pero en realidad ¿qué es moda?
si podemos hacer una definición concreta, la moda es una forma de expresión humana que refleja el contexto sociocultural de la época en la que surge.
tomemos como referencia el power suit. el uso del traje sastre surgió -con una gran influencia de los 80's- gracias al feminismo y a movimientos como #metoo, en el que las mujeres alzan su voz para que sea escuchada y respetada. aunque su uso es cuestión de estilos, el power suit es una respuesta hacia estos movimientos, en el que las mujeres no les importa y se sienten con la entera confianza de usar pantalones -en cortes, texturas y estampados - de inspiración masculina combinándolos con un saco estructurado.
.
.
.
.
.
#notanotherblogmx #moda #tendencias #estilo #fashion #trends #powersuit #minimal #blogging #80s #fashioninspo

text_retweet:
interview with @wtfeminine link in profile✨ #repost ・・・
yes!!! a new episode is out and ready for your ears!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen burris is an incredibly talented memphis artist! she's a singer, songwriter & performer who had used her art to work through some personal trauma. she needed a way to get it out and she found that through her music.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in this episode, jen opens up about being sexually assaulted back in college and the pain of not being believed by the people who are supposed to protect you the most.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kim & jen also discuss the "me too" movement, what a real man looks like, and the importance of setting boundaries.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen also talks about the joy of being a mom and how growing up with an alcoholic & emotionally abusive mother has shaped her own approach to parenting.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
spoiler alert: sometimes our parents teach us the valuable lesson of what not to do as a parent.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kim & jen also discuss all the exciting things on the horizon for jen including writing lyrics & collaborating with other local artists.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen is such a brave woman and this episode is for anyone who has experienced something incredibly painful and has come out on the other side stronger.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
click the link in bio to download and listen to full episode. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
there’s really nothing more to say than what is already on the post. but we’ll expand things a little.
…….
perpetrators shouldn’t be given public platforms. you’re not only sending the message that “we don’t care about what he did,” but you’re also placing additional community members at risk.
…….
it’s shocking to us that communities (i.e. those who are positions of power and decision making) seem to quickly forget how perpetrators used their platform, power, control and privilege to victimize others. where’s the justice for the survivors? where’s the accountability for the perpetrator’s actions?
……..
because as always, perpetrators go back to life as normal and survivors are the ones who have to live with lifetime consequences of the trauma they have endured.
…….
let's not allow this to keep happening.
…….
[image description: a white square image with black text that states perpetrators of sexual violence shouldn't be invited to communities for public speaking engagements.]
……..

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

on january 16, 2019, in the shambhupura village in banswara, rajasthan, india, aarav, 19, and sophia, 18, got married and were cousins but there family, did not like that. the panchayat of shambhupura ordered that couple should be punished, the family of  the couple agreed. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, raped, and killed by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, raped and murder. rajasthan kept the names of the attack hidden. the attackers are only in jail for 3 years. shame on india, rip aarav and sophia.

text:
valentine 11
learning how to say no, is one of the most life-changing gifts you can give yourself.  when we feel less-than, we have a tendency to do everything anyone asks of us, because we don’t want anyone to be upset with us.  people don’t respect you when you don’t respect yourself.  i used to bend over backwards trying to do everything for everyone. i never wanted to upset anyone by saying no—i couldn’t help that time. what that did was make me even unhappier because i felt taken advantage of and i secretly and not-so-secretly resented it and then felt worse about myself for letting people blatantly take advantage of me.  it’s a vicious cycle. helping others is a wonderful thing to do, but not when it becomes codependence. 
if you don’t take care of yourself first, you can’t help anyone else.  boundaries are a beautiful thing.
